    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, STANDARD AND TILT - 2000, 3000, 4000, 8000 - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
            <title>STEERING COLUMN SHAFT BOLTS</title>
            <para>The steering column end yoke pinch bolt assembly should be checked annually or every 50,000 miles
                (80,000 kilometers), whichever comes first. Visually inspect that the plastic collar has been sheared
                off. If the plastic collar is present, tighten the nut until the collar shears off. If the nut appears
                loose, do not tighten it further; install a new nut.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
